{% if file_type == "handler" or file_type == "route" %}
## Focus: Request Path
- Database queries per request (N+1?)
- Unbounded result sets (missing LIMIT/pagination?)
- Blocking I/O in async handler
- Response body size
{% elif file_type == "model" or file_type == "database" %}
## Focus: Data Access
- Missing indexes on queried columns
- Eager loading where lazy would suffice (or vice versa)
- Unnecessary data fetched (SELECT * vs specific columns)
{% elif file_type == "utility" %}
## Focus: Hot Path Potential
- Algorithmic complexity (O(n²) where O(n) or O(n log n) is possible)
- Unnecessary allocations in tight loops
- String concatenation in loops (use join/builder)
{% else %}
## General Review
- Algorithmic efficiency (quadratic where linear is possible)
- Unnecessary re-computation (cache or memoize repeated work)
- Unbounded loops or recursion
- Memory leaks (unclosed resources, growing collections)
- Blocking I/O in async context
{% endif %}

## What NOT to flag
- Code that runs once at startup does not need optimization.
- Micro-optimizations (using `map` vs list comprehension) are not performance issues.
- Code that processes small, bounded datasets does not need pagination.
- Premature optimization suggestions are worse than the problem they claim to solve.

